he test build directory, but there's not enough space on the root. I should check for untracked changes in git as well since we created test files. It could be helpful to suggest setting environment variables, but if the TMPDIR points to a location that’s already limited, that won't help. I think we might need to free up several GB to move forward.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing shared memory issues**\\n\\nI'm noticing a warning about insufficient shared memory, possibly because the `/tmp` directory on the root has no space. This could be why `native-image` is failing when trying to create a temporary directory. I could suggest passing the `-Djava.io.tmpdir` property to Gradle, as that warning suggests. But since the command is coming from a nested Gradle command, I'm unsure if that JVM argument will be properly propagated. For the native-image process, it seems that the Java temp directory might need to be set via the system property `-J-Djava.io.tmpdir`.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "This failure is still environmental, not a test failure.\n\nImportant signals from the log:\n\n```text\n> Task :compileTestJava UP-TO-DATE\n> Task :test UP-TO-DATE\n> Task :nativeTestCompile FAILED\nFatal error: Unable to create temp directory for prefix driverRoot-:\njava.nio.file.FileSystemException: No space left on device\n```\n\nSo the fixed Java tests compile and run. Native Image fails immediately while trying to create its own temp directory, before it can analyze or execute the tests.\n\nNo additional source/test changes are appropriate for this error.\n\nTo proceed, free disk space on the filesystem used by temp files, likely `/tmp` on `/`, then rerun:\n\n```bash\n./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-core:1.8\n```\n\nIf you have another filesystem with enough free space, run with an alternate temp directory:\n\n```bash\nmkdir -p /path/with/free/space/tmp\nTMPDIR=/path/with/free/space/tmp ./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=org.apache.maven.doxia:doxia-core:1.8 -Djava.io.tmpdir=/path/with/free/space/tmp\n```\n\nBut the current error is definitively `No space left on device`, not a Doxia API/test issue.", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg_05f384656a294804016a03170f6d748194a8002e4f358d22d4\",\"phase\":\"final_answer\"}"}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 14990, "output": 795, "cacheRead": 43520, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 59305, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "stop", "timestamp": 1778587389223, "responseId": "resp_05f384656a294804016a0316fee97c81949fd0cc3e6b859f81"}}
